## Documentation Update Protocol

### Trigger: `update documentation for current changes`
1. Collect all changed files
2. Identify affected documents:
   - API changes → API_REFERENCE.md
   - DB schema changes → DATABASE_SCHEMA.md
   - Architecture changes → ARCHITECTURE.md
   - New error codes → ERRORS.md
   - Security changes → SECURITY.md
   - Version release → CHANGELOG.md
3. Update all affected documents
4. Cross-verify consistency between docs and code

### Document Locations
All AI-managed documents live in `.ai.dev/`. Project root `README.md` is human-managed.

|Document|Location|Content|Update Trigger|
|------|------|------|------|
|DECISIONS.md|.ai.dev/|User choices, ADR, bug fix records|Decision changes, bug fixes|
|ARCHITECTURE.md|.ai.dev/|Diagrams, layers, ADR|New modules, pattern changes|
|API_REFERENCE.md|.ai.dev/|Endpoints, schemas|API changes|
|DATABASE_SCHEMA.md|.ai.dev/|ERD, migration history|Schema changes|
|TESTING.md|.ai.dev/|Test execution, coverage|Test strategy changes|
|SECURITY.md|.ai.dev/|Security policy, auth|Security rule changes|
|FRAMEWORK_GUIDELINES.md|.ai.dev/|Framework core rules summary|Framework changes|
|ERRORS.md|.ai.dev/|Error code dictionary|New error codes added|
|CHANGELOG.md|.ai.dev/|Version history (Keep a Changelog)|Every release|

### Diagrams as Code
Use code-based diagrams (not images) for Git traceability:
|Tool|When|
|------|------|
|Mermaid|Simple sequence/flow/ERD (GitHub native)|
|PlantUML|Rich UML (class/component/deployment)|
|Structurizr DSL|C4 model (system context/container/component)|
|D2|Infrastructure/network topology|

### ADR Format
```markdown
# ADR-NNN: <Title>
- Status: Proposed / Accepted / Deprecated / Superseded
- Context: (why this decision is needed)
- Decision: (what was decided)
- Alternatives considered: (options + reasons rejected)
- Consequences: (tradeoffs)
- Date: YYYY-MM-DD
```

### LLM-Friendly Formatting
For critical rules, use structured tags so agents can parse them:
- `<rules type="security" severity="critical">...</rules>` for mandatory security rules
- `<constraints>...</constraints>` for coding conventions
- `<avoid>...</avoid>` for forbidden patterns
- `<recommend>...</recommend>` for suggestions
